<h2>Our quick git guide</h2>
<p>Gtk-gnutella's sourcecode is nowadays hosted on github at 
<a href="https://github.com/gtk-gnutella">https://github.com/gtk-gnutella</a>.
You can clone the git repository with the URL <kbd>https://github.com/gtk-gnutella/gtk-gnutella.git</kbd>.

<h3><a name="quick_guide">Quick guide</a></h3>
<ul>
	<li><kbd>git clone https://github.com/gtk-gnutella/gtk-gnutella.git</kbd></li>
	<li><kbd>cd gtk-gnutella</kbd></li>
	<li><kbd>git checkout -b devel origin/devel</kbd></li>
	<li><kbd>./build.sh</kbd></li>
</ul>
<p>A new build of gtk-gnutella should now be available under src/gtk-gnutella, which
you can now launch with <kbd>./src/gtk-gnutella</kbd>.
</p>
<p>After a while there will be new changes pushed to the origin remote. To fetch
these and build a new version while still in the gtk-gnutella source directory, enter:</p>
<ul>
	<li><kbd>git pull</kbd></li>
	<li><kbd>./build.sh</kbd</li>
</ul>
<p>
Which will also cause a new build of gtk-gnutella to be available under src/gtk-gnutella.
</p>
<p> We need people to test new features and it would be great if you'd test 
this devel branch and report any issues to us at the 
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/p/gtk-gnutella/bugs/">bug tracker</a> 
or by mail at 
<a href="mailto:gtk-gnutella-devel@lists.sourceforge.net">gtk-gnutella-devel@lists.sourceforge.net</a>.
</p>
<p>That's it, read our <a href="?page=git_guide">extended git guide</a>
if you want to know more on how you
can make more use of git, for example if you encounter a bug and want to fix it
yourself.</p>


<h3>Whats in the devel branch to be tested</h3>
<p>
Currently we need help with testing the following features in the devel branch:
<ul>
	<li>IPv6-ready support</li>
</ul>
</p>
